= Custom UART =

== Requirements ==

USB to UART cable (U2U): FTDI Cable 5V VCC-3.3V I/O  https://www.sparkfun.com/products/9717

Logic Level Converter (LLL): http://www.hobbytronics.co.uk/logic-level-converter
                       https://www.sparkfun.com/products/12009

Jumper Wires: https://www.sparkfun.com/products/9194 

Odroid U3 (OU3)

== Connection ==

=== USB2UART Cable to Logic Level Converter ===
USB2UART pinout (FTDI 3.3V IO 5V Vcc Cable.pdf) :
    GND (black)
    CTS (brown)
    VCC (red)
    TXD (orange)
    RXD (yellow)
    RTS (green)

U2U_GND --> LLL_GND
U2U_VCC --> LLL_HV
U2U_TXD --> LLL_RXI
U2U_RXD --> LLL_TXO


=== Logic Level Converter to Odroid U3 ===

LLL_GND --> OU3_GND
LLL_RXO --> OU3_RXD
LLL_TXI --> OU3_TXD 
LLL_LV --> OU3_VCC 


== Use ==

To find the USB port you connected use 'dmesg| tail' and search for ttyUSB (e.g. ttyUSB0)

then you can connect using 'screen':

    # screen /dev/ttyUSB0 115200 8N1

